CDFglobalAttributes.Descriptor: ECT-HOPE-Sci-L2>ECT Helium Oxygen Proton Electron Plasma Analyszer Level 2
CDFglobalAttributes.Logical_source_description: Spin resolved ECT-HOPE science data. Electron fluxes ~15-50,000 eV, ion fluxes ~1-50,000 eV. Electrons and ions measured in alternate spin cadence.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Detector_LABL
Sector_LABL
Energy_LABL
Detector No.
Sector No.
Collapse method used for a given pixel.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: For a given pixel, the number of spin angle sectors which are collapsed on board to fit the telemetry allocation. The collapse method sums all values together, then compresses according to the following algorithm: if (sum < 16384) {return sum} else {return ((sum-16384)/64) + 16384}

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ESA_Volt_LABL_1
Acquisition_Period
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The length of a single ESA step acquisition

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Science data acquisition Plan
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Which science plan was used for the acquisition.  The seclected science plan determines the ESA Sweep, TOF DAC, data product selection, and data collapse method used for an acquisition.  As a general rule, plans 0-7 & 15 are reserved for HOPE nominal operations, and 8-14 are reserved for burst support operations.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Plan_Step
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Which step within a science plan was used.  Each science plan consists of up to 16 steps, each of which can specify different HVPS and telemetry configuration settings.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ESA_Volt
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Absolute values of the ESA voltage that was used for each energy step.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Default time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Epoch at times of ion mode measurements

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Half sample time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Half the HOPE frame time

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Default time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Epoch at times of electron mode measurements

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Half sample time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Half the HOPE frame time

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Polarity of the ESA voltage.
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Polarity of the ESA voltage.  0 = positive (electron mode), 1 = negative (ion mode)

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ESA_Sweep
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Which of the 16 ESA Sweep ptables was used for the acquisition.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Counter Energy Collapse
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Whether or not energy collapsing was enabled for Counters (starts, stops, H+, He+, O+, e-, etc.) data. 0 = collapsed, 1 = not collapsed.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: [CreateCDF ONLY] FPDU: Differential directional proton flux ~15-50,000 eV (5 Detectors, 16 Sectors, 72 Energies)
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Proton flux as a function of detector pixel (5), spin angle sector (16), and energy (72).  Note that data have been expanded to the highest possible resolution (16 spin angles, 72 energies), even though in most cases the transmitted data are collapsed (36 energies, 4-8-16-8-4 spin angles) to fit the telemetry allocation.

Flag type descriptions
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Description of each flag.

VarData: Count rate issue. 0:at least 10 counts in this sample; 1: 10>counts>=3; 2: 3>counts>=1; 3: flux below the one-count level.
Eclipse. 0: s/c not in eclipse; 1: s/c in eclipse at time of measurement.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Flags on ion data
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flags to indicate potential issues with the ion data. Each element of this array contains the flag status for a particular concern. A flag value of zero indicates no unusual concerns of that type for that time sample. Increasing flag values indicate increasing concern. See FLAGS variable for a description of each element.
x_LABLAXES: Count rate issue. 0:at least 10 counts in this sample; 1: 10>counts>=3; 2: 3>counts>=1; 3: flux below the one-count level.
Eclipse. 0: s/c not in eclipse; 1: s/c in eclipse at time of measurement.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: Flags on electron data
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Flags to indicate potential issues with electron data. Each element of this array contains the flag status for a particular concern. A flag value of zero indicates no unusual concerns of that type for that time sample. Increasing flag values indicate increasing concern. See FLAGS variable for a description of each element.
x_LABLAXES: Count rate issue. 0:at least 10 counts in this sample; 1: 10>counts>=3; 2: 3>counts>=1; 3: flux below the one-count level.
Eclipse. 0: s/c not in eclipse; 1: s/c in eclipse at time of measurement.
